                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n\t\t\t\t<placeName>New York</placeName>\n\t\t\t\t<date>Novr 24<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1859</date>\n\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t<p>My Dear Sir</p>\n\t\t\t<p rend=\"indent(2)\">I beg you will pardon my seeming neglect<lb/> in not writing you at\n\t\t\t\tan earlier date but the truth<lb/> is I have been so busily occupied of late that I\n\t\t\t\thave<lb/> not had scarce a moments leisure time; this day<lb/> being\n\t\t\t\t\t<date>Thanksgiving Day</date>, and the Courts and lawyers'<lb/> offices being\n\t\t\t\tclosed, I have determined to devote the best<lb/> portion of it to my correspondents\n\t\t\t\tsome of whose letters I<lb/> have unanswered for nearly a year.</p>\n\t\t\t<p rend=\"indent(1)\">I therefore begin with the most esteemed—yourself, my<lb/> dear and\n\t\t\t\tmuch respected friend.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>I sent you a printed report of the decision &amp;c in your suite<lb/> against\n\t\t\t\t\t<persName>Frank</persName> and <persName>Sklarz</persName> and on the\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<date>17<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> inst<lb/> a package by Adams Express\n\t\t\t\tcontaining five copies of<lb/> the printed edition of your Pentateuch.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>We have settled now with all but <persName>Sklarz</persName>, and I<lb/> am satisfied\n\t\t\t\t\t<hi rend=\"underline\">he</hi> has not ten dollars which could be<lb/> collected\n\t\t\t\tof him by way of damages, or costs.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Against each and all of them injunctions had to be<lb/> obtained and have been\n\t\t\t\tobtained.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>With <persName>Ottinger</persName>, as you are already aware, we settled for\n\t\t\t\t$100<lb/> cash. With <persName>Ettinger</persName> &amp;\n\t\t\t\t\t<persName>Gotthold</persName>—as you advised—<lb/> $50 in cash, and their note\n\t\t\t\tat 6 months for $50. &amp; forfeit the books<lb/>\n\t\t\t\t<persName>Frank</persName> could pay but $32.50 (he is out of business now)<lb/> and\n\t\t\t\t\t<persName>Sklarz</persName> has not paid and cannot pay anything</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g44j978/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
