                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I give you all these figures that you may see <hi rend=\"underline\">exactly</hi><lb/>\n\t\t\t\thow the matter has resulted, as you might otherwise<lb/> have forgotten that there\n\t\t\t\twere any disbursements<lb/> to be made, thinking only of the receipts: for<lb/>\n\t\t\t\t<persName>Uncle David</persName> said to my mother while she was in\n\t\t\t\t\t<placeName>Phila</placeName><lb/> that “he had heard that <hi rend=\"underline\"\n\t\t\t\t\t>I</hi> had received $100 from<lb/> one of your clients, and as I had not sent\n\t\t\t\tyou any<lb/> portion of it, I must have enjoyed a fine <sic>yomtale</sic> with\n\t\t\t\tit.”<lb/> Of course I do not mind the remarks of third parties<lb/> but it is as\n\t\t\t\twell that things should be properly understood<lb/> and such remarks could not then\n\t\t\t\tbe made.</p>\n\t\t\t<p rend=\"indent(1)\">I hope the books reached you safely. <persName>Frank</persName>\n\t\t\t\thas<lb/> one copy which he promised to send me, but he has<lb/> failed to do so.</p>\n\t\t\t<p rend=\"indent(1)\">With <persName>Heller</persName> in\n\t\t\t\t\t<placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> we can do nothing here.<lb/> A friend of mine\n\t\t\t\thas written me that he, <persName>Heller</persName>, is an<lb/> old man and very\n\t\t\t\tpoor, and nothing could be done with<lb/> him. If you are acquainted with a lawyer\n\t\t\t\tthere<lb/> and are disposed to proceed against <persName>Heller</persName>. I\n\t\t\t\tcan<lb/> furnish you with copies of the papers all ready prepared<lb/> which would\n\t\t\t\tsave you much expense; or if you desire<lb/> it, <hi rend=\"underline\">I</hi> will\n\t\t\t\twrite <persName>Heller</persName> a very strong letter and<lb/> send him a copy of\n\t\t\t\tthe printed report of the decision<lb/> of the Court in your suits against the\n\t\t\t\tparties in this city<lb/> which may have the effect of frightening him out of<lb/>\n\t\t\t\tthe nefarious business and have the trouble and<lb/> expense of proceeding against\n\t\t\t\thim legally for an<lb/>\n\t\t\t\t<sic>an</sic> injunction. Please let me know your</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g44j978/canvas/p3"
                }
